Except she can't see out of them.

344
00:16:09,935 --> 00:16:12,062
So she says.

345
00:16:12,171 --> 00:16:13,536
You find anything on the MRI?

346
00:16:13,605 --> 00:16:15,402
No sign of plaques. It's not MS.

347
00:16:15,507 --> 00:16:17,498
We haven't found anything
abnormal on any tests.

348
00:16:17,576 --> 00:16:19,100
Except she can't see or move her hands.

349
00:16:19,178 --> 00:16:20,236
So she says.

350
00:16:20,346 --> 00:16:22,473
You can't lie about flaccid paralysis.

351
00:16:23,882 --> 00:16:26,874
Maybe she's not lying. Her brain is.

352
00:16:26,952 --> 00:16:29,216
What if it's a conversion disorder?

353
00:16:29,288 --> 00:16:31,188
Lacks personal boundaries.

354
00:16:32,591 --> 00:16:36,857
Promiscuous. Inappropriate
obsession with truth telling.

355
00:16:36,929 --> 00:16:38,726
Certainly sounds like a psych case.

356
00:16:39,765 --> 00:16:42,962
Cool. I'll set up a psych consult
and start her on anti-depressants.

357
00:16:43,068 --> 00:16:44,296
No.

358
00:16:46,071 --> 00:16:48,266
Her mind is tricking her body.

359
00:16:49,541 --> 00:16:50,906
We need to trick her mind.

360
00:16:52,478 --> 00:16:54,241
Or even better...

361
