380
00:17:51,503 --> 00:17:55,405
If you show doubt, the
placebo treatment won't work.

381
00:17:55,474 --> 00:17:58,170
If it's just depression,
that's good news, right?

382
00:17:58,277 --> 00:17:59,505
There are a lot of great medications.

383
00:17:59,611 --> 00:18:02,944
Why can't we just give her those?
Why do we have to lie to her?

384
00:18:03,015 --> 00:18:05,449
Because we might be wrong.

385
00:18:05,517 --> 00:18:09,977
Those medications take a long time to work,
and since your mom's condition's declining,

386
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:12,990
there's a chance the drugs won't
tell us anything until it's too late.

387
00:18:14,860 --> 00:18:16,521
My mom's not depressed.

388
00:18:16,628 --> 00:18:18,220
Maybe she's hiding it from you.

389
00:18:18,297 --> 00:18:19,696
No.

390
00:18:19,798 --> 00:18:20,787
She wouldn't.

391
00:18:20,866 --> 00:18:22,094
She's doing what every good mom does.

392
00:18:22,167 --> 00:18:25,136
Protecting her child from bad news
that she can't do anything about.

393
00:18:25,204 --> 00:18:26,671
My mom's never lied to me.

394
00:18:26,772 --> 00:18:28,103
If you don't know how to lie,

395
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:31,235
you don't know how to tell
when you're being lied to.

396
00:18:35,547 --> 00:18:37,845
Maybe you're right.

397
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:39,383
I know I'm... I was lying.

398
00:18:40,552 --> 00:18:41,917
I know how to lie.

399
00:18:43,188 --> 00:18:45,554
I just won't do it to my mother.

400
00:18:51,463 --> 00:18:53,226
You like foosball?

401
00:18:55,134 --> 00:18:58,228
Until the treatment of your
infectious paraparesis takes effect,

402
00:18:58,337 --> 00:18:59,861
Jane can't come back into the room.

403
00:18:59,972 --> 00:19:01,234
