I did not screw up. The
density is consistent.

593
00:29:18,656 --> 00:29:22,023
Just means the density was
consistent. Doesn't mean it was cold.

594
00:29:22,127 --> 00:29:24,527
It's possible all she has are hot spots.

595
00:29:25,063 --> 00:29:28,191
It's consistent because her entire
skeleton is turning to stone.

596
00:29:31,469 --> 00:29:33,130
Good for an aspiring superhero.

597
00:29:33,738 --> 00:29:36,298
Fatal for a human hoping
to make it to Kwanzaa.

598
00:29:36,374 --> 00:29:38,842
It's got to be from a carbonic
anhydrase type 2 deficiency.

599
00:29:38,910 --> 00:29:39,968
It has free will.

600
00:29:40,044 --> 00:29:41,409
It doesn't have to be
anything it doesn't want to be.

601
00:29:41,479 --> 00:29:44,073
I meant if it's not CA-2, well,

602
00:29:44,182 --> 00:29:47,117
none of the other causes of
osteopetrosis are treatable.

603
00:29:51,556 --> 00:29:52,682
You're right. It's got to be.

604
00:29:53,224 --> 00:29:56,682
Go run her blood and hope that
your sunny optimism isn't misplaced.

605
00:30:04,369 --> 00:30:08,237
They accused Kutner of screwing
up a test because they hate him.

606
00:30:08,339 --> 00:30:09,397
You're surprised?

607
00:30:09,507 --> 00:30:10,633
That's the sort of crap that happens

608
00:30:10,708 --> 00:30:12,300
when you mess with people's heads.

609
00:30:12,377 --> 00:30:14,106
One day, he will screw up a test.

610
00:30:14,946 --> 00:30:18,382
And if they don't accuse him of that
because they like him, someone could die.

611
00:30:20,852 --> 00:30:21,876
Where are we going?

612
00:30:21,953 --> 00:30:23,386
Nowhere. I just know it hurts you.

613
00:30:26,858 --> 00:30:30,624
CA-2 deficiency's a genetic
disorder that scrambles proteins.

614
00:30:30,728 --> 00:30:34,255
If the blood test is positive,
you'll need a bone marrow transplant.

615
00:30:34,365 --> 00:30:36,993
"Transplant" sounds like a
euphemism for "slim odds. "

616
00:30:37,969 --> 00:30:40,631
Slim but not none.

617
00:30:42,740 --> 00:30:44,867
We're gonna need to
test Jane for a match.

618
00:30:45,610 --> 00:30:46,736
Don't you have donor banks?

619
00:30:46,811 --> 00:30:48,073
Jane is your best bet.

620
00:30:48,146 --> 00:30:50,080
The procedure is perfectly
safe. There's no risk.

621
00:30:50,148 --> 00:30:51,547
No risk?

622
00:30:52,150 --> 00:30:54,846
Any surgery has... Then,
don't tell me there's no risk.

623
00:30:55,820 --> 00:30:58,311
You're gonna tell me
there's no pain, either?

624
00:30:58,423 --> 00:30:59,549
The testing will hurt a little.

625
00:30:59,624 --> 00:31:01,615
I'll be fine.

626
00:31:04,262 --> 00:31:07,595
If she doesn't do this
and you don't make it,

627
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:10,893
she's gonna spend the rest
of her life blaming herself.

628
00:31:14,138 --> 00:31:16,436
Mom, please.

629
00:31:20,011 --> 00:31:21,808
Find someone else.

630
00:31:23,414 --> 00:31:25,041
Let someone else take the risk.

631
00:31:35,960 --> 00:31:38,292
Donor bank turned up a
49-year-old man in Cleveland

632
00:31:38,363 --> 00:31:40,297
who's a five out of six HLA match.

633
00:31:40,365 --> 00:31:41,662
First flight out of
Cleveland leaves at...

634
00:31:41,766 --> 00:31:45,202
Why is a 49-year-old Cleveland man
a closer match than her daughter?

635
00:31:45,303 --> 00:31:47,771
He may not be. Maggie
didn't let us test her.

636
00:31:47,839 --> 00:31:48,828
Why not?

637
00:31:48,907 --> 00:31:50,534
Pain, danger, risk of...

638
00:31:50,608 --> 00:31:52,303
Only reason to give multiple reasons

639
00:31:52,377 --> 00:31:54,675
is you're searching for what
the person wants to hear.

640
00:31:58,349 --> 00:31:59,646
House.

641
00:32:08,326 --> 00:32:09,987
You're wrong about sainted Mommy.

642
00:32:10,061 --> 00:32:13,861
Don't care. You can forget the donor
bank. There's no CA-2 deficiency.

643
00:32:13,965 --> 00:32:15,523
Best we can do is make her comfortable.

644
00:32:19,504 --> 00:32:20,801
Is that from Taub?

645
00:32:21,472 --> 00:32:22,632
Yes.

646
00:32:23,174 --> 00:32:24,573
Yes, it is.

647
00:32:29,147 --> 00:32:30,307
Merry Christmas.

648
00:32:31,916 --> 00:32:33,747
Who's gonna tell the
patient she's dying?

649
00:32:35,753 --> 00:32:37,015
I will.

650
00:32:37,989 --> 00:32:40,924
And nobody leaves here until
we find out what killed her.

651
00:32:48,066 --> 00:32:50,364
Whatever she has is fatal.

652
00:32:50,435 --> 00:32:53,927
Makes no difference if it's
disease number 58 or 907.

653
00:32:56,841 --> 00:32:58,240
Are you guys mad at me?

654
00:32:58,343 --> 00:33:00,743
No. You had no choice.

655
00:33:00,845 --> 00:33:03,245
Of course I had a choice. You had
no choice once I made my choice.

656
00:33:03,348 --> 00:33:05,509
And now, I'm choosing
not to be mad at you.

657
00:33:05,583 --> 00:33:06,572
Why?

658
00:33:06,651 --> 00:33:07,948
Because it will drive House nuts.

659
00:33:11,089 --> 00:33:13,182
Do you think that will make
your lives better or worse?

660
00:33:16,928 --> 00:33:18,759
I told my mom I don't
care what she thinks.

661
00:33:19,030 --> 00:33:20,588
I want you to test my marrow.

662
00:33:25,737 --> 00:33:27,762
I can't be dying.

663
00:33:27,872 --> 00:33:28,896
Sure you can.

664
00:33:28,973 --> 00:33:30,235
You're wrong.

665
00:33:30,908 --> 00:33:32,808
You don't even know what I have.

666
00:33:32,910 --> 00:33:36,869
What you have is one last
Christmas with your daughter.

667
00:33:36,948 --> 00:33:38,882
One last chance to give her a present.

668
00:33:40,385 --> 00:33:42,250
The truth.

669
00:33:42,320 --> 00:33:45,221
It's inexpensive, highly valued.

670
00:33:45,289 --> 00:33:47,883
Never have to stand in line to
return it the day after Christmas.

671
00:33:47,959 --> 00:33:49,551
What are you talking about?

672
00:33:50,495 --> 00:33:52,258
A mother who's going to die

673
00:33:52,330 --> 00:33:55,390
doesn't refuse a donor
test because it might hurt.

674
00:33:55,466 --> 00:33:58,458
She refuses when she
knows it won't match.

675
00:33:59,670 --> 00:34:00,830
Which tends to happen

676
00:34:00,938 --> 00:34:04,396
when mother and daughter
aren't mother and daughter.

677
00:34:10,782 --> 00:34:14,274
I can do DNA tests if you'd
rather keep lying to me.

678
00:34:19,824 --> 00:34:21,655
I never wanted kids.

679
00:34:23,928 --> 00:34:27,022
I loved them, but with my genes...

680
00:34:27,131 --> 00:34:30,430
I knew this woman, a drug addict.

681
00:34:33,004 --> 00:34:36,337
She got pregnant, didn't
want to have an abortion.

682
00:34:37,708 --> 00:34:40,802
But she also didn't want her daughter
to ever know who her real mother was.

683
00:34:42,480 --> 00:34:44,004
What she was.

684
00:34:45,950 --> 00:34:48,009
I promised never to tell.

685
00:34:53,558 --> 00:34:56,857
A promise to an addict is worth
more than a promise to your daughter?

686
00:34:56,961 --> 00:34:58,690
It'd be cruel to tell her.

687
00:34:58,796 --> 00:35:02,789
Right. She lives a lie.
You get to die a hypocrite.

688
00:35:07,171 --> 00:35:10,868
Mom? The doctors told
me what's happening.

689
00:35:10,975 --> 00:35:13,205
It's gonna be okay, sweetheart.

690
00:35:13,311 --> 00:35:14,573
I promise you.

691
00:35:15,746 --> 00:35:16,872
Doctors can be wrong.

692
00:35:18,015 --> 00:35:19,346
There's still a chance I can beat...

693
00:35:19,417 --> 00:35:21,351
You really believe that?

694
00:35:27,391 --> 00:35:28,551
I do.

695
00:35:29,894 --> 00:35:32,362
No, Mom. You're dying.

696
00:35:33,397 --> 00:35:35,331
Nobody can help you.

697
00:35:38,703 --> 00:35:40,728
It's not gonna be okay.

698
00:36:02,927 --> 00:36:04,155
That was cold.

699
00:36:04,228 --> 00:36:05,559
Yeah.

700
00:36:28,052 --> 00:36:29,986
What did you get for Christmas?

701
00:36:30,087 --> 00:36:32,681
I got a watch, a vintage LP,

702
00:36:32,757 --> 00:36:35,248
and a second edition Conan Doyle.

703
00:36:35,326 --> 00:36:37,521
And if that wasn't bad
enough, my patient's dying.

704
00:36:38,629 --> 00:36:41,723
Christmas deaths in a hospital.
There's nothing more depressing.

705
00:36:41,799 --> 00:36:43,790
No one ever wants to go
in the patient's room.

706
00:36:43,901 --> 00:36:46,802
Even the candy stripers
leave them alone.

707
00:36:48,272 --> 00:36:49,762
But I saw something amazing.

708
00:36:51,576 --> 00:36:53,066
Pure truth.

709
00:36:54,078 --> 00:36:56,512
She told her mother that she was dying.

710
00:36:56,614 --> 00:36:58,309
Stripped her of all hope.

711
00:36:59,183 --> 00:37:01,651
That sounds horrible.

712
00:37:01,752 --> 00:37:04,812
It was like watching some
bizarre astronomical event

713
00:37:04,922 --> 00:37:06,514
that you know you're
never gonna see again.

714
00:37:06,624 --> 00:37:10,617
You tell people the cold, hard truth
all the time. You get off on it.

715
00:37:10,695 --> 00:37:12,026
Because I don't care.

716
00:37:12,096 --> 00:37:13,358
She cared.

717
00:37:13,831 --> 00:37:15,924
And she did it, anyway.

718
00:37:17,134 --> 00:37:19,432
She did it because she cared.

719
00:37:21,205 --> 00:37:25,301
The angels of Christmas have finally
given House a present he can appreciate.

720
00:37:25,376 --> 00:37:26,468
Oh, don't ruin it.

721
00:37:26,544 --> 00:37:29,035
Don't pin this on Christ.
He's got enough nails in him.

722
00:37:29,113 --> 00:37:30,273
Patient had to die...

723
00:37:30,348 --> 00:37:31,610
Why don't you take off that hat?

724
00:37:31,682 --> 00:37:33,775
It's Christmas. It's a reindeer.

725
00:37:33,851 --> 00:37:35,978
It's a moose, on a Jew.

726
00:37:36,053 --> 00:37:37,452
Who cares?

727
00:37:41,025 --> 00:37:42,287
Things have their place.

728
00:37:42,360 --> 00:37:45,158
You wouldn't hang dreidels
from a Christmas tree.

729
00:37:45,229 --> 00:37:46,628
You could.

730
00:37:47,698 --> 00:37:49,461
Things don't care.

731
00:37:54,005 --> 00:37:55,870
No, they don't.

732
00:37:59,677 --> 00:38:01,668
Happy solstice, House.

733
00:38:02,813 --> 00:38:05,475
<i>God rest ye merry gentlemen</i>

734
00:38:05,549 --> 00:38:07,983
<i>Let nothing you dismay</i>

735
00:38:08,052 --> 00:38:11,044
<i>Remember, Christ, our savior</i>

736
00:38:11,155 --> 00:38:13,555
<i>Was born on Christmas day</i>

737
00:38:13,658 --> 00:38:15,990
<i>To save us all from Satan's power</i>

738
00:38:16,060 --> 00:38:18,927
<i>When we were gone astray</i>

739
00:38:19,030 --> 00:38:20,895
